author: tomj
msg: Fix a problem with Skeletons and WSDL generation:
The getOperationDescs() and getOperationDescByName()
APIs were showing up in WSDL when skeletons were
turned on.
Fix: Filter out static methods when creating the
method list for a service.
NOTE TO IBM: You may want this for Beta 3 if you care
about the WSDL generated when using skeletons!

author: gdaniels
msg: Merge fix from beta-3 - don't write Holder types to schema, write
the held type.

author: gdaniels
msg: Merge WSDD fixes over from beta-3

author: gdaniels
msg: Simple fix for bug 10103.
Don't write Holder types when emitting WSDL/Schema, instead use the
held type.
Also, make sure ParameterDesc is consistent - always use the Java
Class of the actual parameter.

author: gdaniels
msg: Fix WSDD to correctly instantiate chains with type="" attributes.
This was preventing authentication from actually functioning - we should
add negative tests to make sure bad user/passwords actually throw
faults!
Fix JAXRPC test to use authentication, since it's needed now.
Remove authentication from attachments test.
